# Patches Lazarus applied during resurrection:
#   - makefile: append -lm after the object list in each executable link rule (modern ld is link-order sensitive, so -lm placed before objects via LFLAGS was discarded, causing undefined references to exp/sqrt/sincos).
#   - src/fpout.c: replaced two self-referential sprintf calls (sprintf(out_path, "%s/%s", out_path, pdb_code) and sprintf(out_path, "%s/pockets", out_path)) with a scratch-buffer snprintf+strcpy. Overlapping source/dest in sprintf is undefined behavior; on modern glibc it collapsed out_path to empty, so fpocket tried to mkdir /pockets and silently wrote no pocket files.
#   - Build flags: CFLAGS='-std=gnu89 -Wno-error=implicit-function-declaration -Wno-error=implicit-int -Wno-error' (and QCFLAGS='-O -std=gnu89 -Wno-error' for bundled Qhull) so 2010 C compiles under GCC 13. Built only the 'fpocket' target (skipped mdpocket/netcdf).

